User Stories for Messaging App

1. User Registration- Must Have
	• As a new user
	• I want to sign up with a new username
	• So that I can create an account to use the app

	• Effort Level: 3

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	A form to fill in for username and password
		When:	I fill in information
		Then:	I have a new account

2. User Login - Must Have
	• As a returning user
	• I want to log in with my credentials
	• So that I can access my messages and contacts

	• Effort Level: 3

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	A log in form for username and password
		When:	I fill in information
		Then:	I get logged in and redirected to home page or get an invalid credentials message

3. Send a Message - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to send a text message to a contact
	• So that I can communicate with them in real-time

	• Effort Level: 5

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	You have an existing conversation and a blank form to enter a text message
		When:	I type and submit a message
		Then:	The message is saved to the database

4. Receive Messages - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to receive messages instantly
	• So that I can have real-time conversations

	• Effort Level: 8

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	You are in an existing conversation
		When:	Someone else sends you a message
		Then:	You receive the message in real-time

5. Contact List - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to view a list of my contacts
	• So that I can choose who to message

	• Effort Level: 3

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I have previously added contact(s)
		When:	I click a button for my contacts list
		Then:	I view the entire list of my contact usernames	

7. Chat History - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to view previous messages in a conversation
	• So that I can refer back to past communication

	• Effort Level: 5

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I have an existing conversation 
		When:	I click the button for that conversation
		Then:	I view the conversation in the order the messages were sent (if easy to implement, add pagination, otherwise separate story)

8. Logout - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to log out of my account
	• So that I can secure my information on shared devices

	• Effort Level: 2

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I want to sign out of the application.
		When:	I click the logout button.
		Then:	The server is notified and I am redirected to the landing page.

9. Database for Messages - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to view messages that have already been sent/received
	• So that I can see chat history

	• Effort Level: 5

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I have already sent and/or received messages
		When:	I open a conversation
		Then:	The server sends and the front end displays the message history with that contact

10. Database for Contacts - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to view my contacts that have already been added
	• So that I can view our chat history and send additional messages

	• Effort Level: 3

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I already have 1 or more contacts
		When:	I open my address book
		Then:	The server sends and the front end displays a list of my contacts

11. Start a conversation - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to start a conversation with an existing contact
	• So that I can send and receive messages with them

	• Effort Level: 8

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I have an eixsting contact with no message history
		When:	I click to send them a message
		Then:	The server starts a web socket connection with the contact and the front end displays the conversation page

12. Verify new username does not already exist - Must Have
	• As a user
	• I want to select login credentials
	• So that I can use the rest of the app

	• Effort Level: 2

	• Acceptance Criteria
		Given:	I have supplied a potential username
		When:	I click to check if the username is available
		Then:	The server verifies whether the username is available in the credentials database and notifies me of the result


